From: intp-comparison <noreply@example.invalid>
Subject: [PATCH] MLClassifier: read project_folder from INTP_R_FOLDER env

Replace the hostname-hardcoded R folder paths in MLClassifier.java with
env-var loading. The upstream Meyer version hardcodes paths for the
build host ("vinicius-desktop", "DESKTOP-OTD5GFM", "pantana01"); this
patch adds a single env-var probe that takes precedence over the
hostname dispatch.

Reads:
  - INTP_R_FOLDER   : path to <CloudSimInterference>/R (with or
                      without trailing slash)
  - INTP_R_LIBPATHS : R user library (passed as .libPaths(...))

Already-present check: setup-iada.sh greps for "INTP_R_FOLDER" in the
target file and skips this patch silently when the fork (e.g.
ggrv-intp/CloudSimInterference) already carries the change.

Apply with:
  git apply bench/iada/patches/mlclassifier-env-vars.patch
or (from outside a git tree):
  patch -p1 < bench/iada/patches/mlclassifier-env-vars.patch

Rebuild CloudSim (mvn package / your toolchain) after applying.

---
 src/cloudsim/interference/MLClassifier.java | 9 +++++++++
 1 file changed, 9 insertions(+)

diff --git a/src/cloudsim/interference/MLClassifier.java b/src/cloudsim/interference/MLClassifier.java
--- a/src/cloudsim/interference/MLClassifier.java
+++ b/src/cloudsim/interference/MLClassifier.java
@@ -88,6 +88,15 @@ public class MLClassifier {

 		// Log.printLine("=======" + hostname);
 		// usar R para classificar ....
+
+		String envFolder = System.getenv("INTP_R_FOLDER");
+		String envLibPaths = System.getenv("INTP_R_LIBPATHS");
+		if (envFolder != null && !envFolder.isEmpty()) {
+			project_folder = envFolder.endsWith("/") ? envFolder : envFolder + "/";
+			if (envLibPaths != null && !envLibPaths.isEmpty()) {
+				re.eval(".libPaths('" + envLibPaths + "')");
+			}
+		}
 		if (hostname.equals("vinicius-desktop")) {
 			project_folder = "/home/vinicius/git/CloudSimInterference/R/"; // ubuntu
 			re.eval(".libPaths('/home/vinicius/R/x86_64-pc-linux-gnu-library/3.6')"); // ubuntu
